jo4neo
Annotation Type neo

@Target(value={FIELD,TYPE})
@Retention(value=RUNTIME)
public @interface neo

Defines a persistent field, including primitive types or arrays of primitives, complex types, and collections of complex types. (Arrays of complex types are not supported).

Author:
Taylor Cowan

Optional Element Summary
 boolean index
          If true the field will be indexed by jo4neo.
 java.lang.String inverse
          Name of a relationship for which this field acts as inverse.
 boolean recency
          If true jo4neo manages a list of instances in most recent order.
 java.lang.Class<? extends TraverserProvider> traverser
          Declares a TraverserProvider from which the field (of type Collection) will be generated.
 java.lang.String value
          If the value is specified, the node property or relationship will be named accordingly.
 

value

public abstract java.lang.String value
If the value is specified, the node property or relationship will be named accordingly. Defaults to the qualified field name.

Returns:
Default:
"default"

index

public abstract boolean index
If true the field will be indexed by jo4neo. It is the client's responsibility to ensure uniqueness, as jo4neo allows multiple entities to be indexed against a single value. Defaults to false.

Returns:
Default:
false

inverse

public abstract java.lang.String inverse
Name of a relationship for which this field acts as inverse. All incoming edges with the same name will be treated as if they were outgoing.

Returns:
Default:
"default"

traverser

public abstract java.lang.Class<? extends TraverserProvider> traverser
Declares a TraverserProvider from which the field (of type Collection) will be generated.

Returns:
Default:
jo4neo.DefaultTraverserProvider.class

recency

public abstract boolean recency
If true jo4neo manages a list of instances in most recent order.

See Also:
ObjectGraph.getMostRecent(Class, int)
Default:
false
